   <text>
      <body>
         
            
               <p>
                        <persName>Mary Goldhawk</persName>, daughter of <persName>Ambrose
                     Goldhawk</persName> and <persName>Margaret Goldhawk</persName> of
                     <placeName>Staines, Middlesex</placeName>, was born in <date when="1710">1710</date>. On <date when="1734-01-15">Jan. 15, 1734</date> she married
                     <persName>Anthony Vazeille</persName> (c. <date from="1706" to="1747">1706–47</date>), a <placeName>London</placeName> merchant. Both were of
                  Huguenot descent. She likely came to know the Wesley brothers after the death of
                  her husband, through the Perronets (See <persName>
                            <ptr target="/persons/pers2176.xml"/>CW</persName>'s Journal, <date when="1749-07-20">July 20, 1749</date>). On <date when="1751-02-18">Feb. 18,
                     1751</date> she and <persName>
                            <ptr target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> were married. Both the initial warmth and the progressive
                  tensions of their married life are displayed in <persName>
                            <ptr target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>'s letters to
                     <persName>Mary</persName> that survive.</p>
            
         
